\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 28. L. roseus} Steven,{\i   Mém. Soc. Nat. Moscou}{\b  4}: 92 (1813). Glabrous perennial; stem 40-150 cm, not winged. Leaves without tendril; leaflets 1 pair, 25-50 × 15-35 mm, ovate-elliptical to obovate-orbicular, pinnately veined; stipules 4-15 mm, linear-triangular. Racemes 1- to 5-flowered. Calyx-teeth unequal; corolla 12-20 mm, pink. Legume 30-55 × 5-9 mm, pale brown, glabrous. Seeds up to 10, smooth; hilum 1/5 of the circumference.{\i   Krym.} Rs (K). ({\i  Anatolia and Caucasus}.)
\par

