\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 35. L. tremolsianus} Pau,{\i   Not. Bot. Fl. Esp.}{\b  4}: 29 (1891) ({\i  L. elegans} Porta & Rigo, non Vogler,{\i   L. latifolius} var.{\i   angustifolius} sensu Willk. pro parte). Glabrous annual; stem up to 100 cm, winged. Leaflets 1 pair, 30-100 × 1-4 mm, linear-lanceolate; stipules 10-30 × 2-4 mm, linear-lanceolate, semi-sagittate. Racemes 1- to 3-flowered. Calyx-teeth subequal, at least the lower longer than tube; corolla 20-30 mm, pink with blue wings. Legume c. 70 × 6 mm, glabrous. •{\i   S.E. Spain.} Hs.
