\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 36. L. tingitanus} L., {\i  Sp. Pl. }732 (1753). Glabrous annual; stem 60-120 cm, winged. Leaflets 1 pair, 20-80 × 4-18 mm, linear-lanceolate to ovate; stipules 12-25 × 3-12 mm, lanceolate to ovate, semi-sagittate or -hastate. Racemes 1- to 3-flowered. Calyx-teeth subequal, shorter than tube; corolla 20-30 mm, bright purple. Legume 60-100 × 8-10 mm, brown, glabrous. Seeds 6-8, smooth; hilum 1/6 of the circumference. {\i  S. & E. part of Iberian peninsula; Sardegna; Açores.} Az Hs Lu Sa.
\par

