\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 37. L. odoratus} L.,{\i   Sp. Pl}. 732 (1753). More or less pubescent annual; stem 50-200 cm, winged. Leaflets 1 pair, 20-60 × 7-30 mm, ovate-oblong or elliptical, sometimes feebly parallel veined; stipules 15-25 × 3-4 mm, lanceolate, semi-sagittate. Racemes 1- to 3-flowered. Calyx-teeth subequal, longer than tube; corolla 20-35 mm, purple. Legume 50-70 × 10-12 mm, brown, pubescent. Seeds c. 8, smooth; hilum ¼ of the circumference. 2n = 14.  •{\i   S. Italy and Sicilia; widely cultivated for ornament and perhaps naturalized in some parts of C. & S. Europe.} It Si [Au Ga Lu].
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   In cultivation the corolla may be white, pink, purple, violet or blue or some combination of these; some of these colour variants may occasionally occur as casuals.
